review: I like Chilis and frequent this chain often but this visit sucked.  Me and two friends went in for an early dinner. I ordered a steak cooked rare, it came out medium and it was very tough. One of my friends ordered a burger and the bun was very nearly burnt, overdone. For some reason it took almost an hour to get our food (it wasn't that busy). I had to request a knife with my steak (thought that was a no brainer) and I had to ask for Â spoon for my friend who ordered tacos that came with a side of beans. Also at the end of the meal we asked for our check and a to-go box and then the waitress repeated it back to us with an attitude like it was the most inconvenient thing we could possibly ask for.

Chili's has pretty tasty food, but I tend to feel like crap after eating here. I think the food is super greasy or something. I eat out a lot, but tend to try to order stuff that isn't too unhealthy.  Service is hit or miss.
it is not a fajita if doesn't have beans, rice and guacamole....the chicken was too white and plain...it is not mexican food.
